descript.abstract: Tax Parcels Previous Deed Lines for Gaston County, North Carolina Vector Data
descript.purpose: It's purpose is to display the changes or history of parcels lines geographically.

idinfo.accconst: This layer is a read-only layer.
idinfo.useconst: The feature data provided by Gaston County is made available on the condition that the user willingly agrees to waive any and all claims against Gaston County, its contractors, and/or its employees. By accessing this data you are releasing Gaston County, its contractors, and its employees from all liability that may occur from any omissions, errors, or inaccuracies in the data. This data may not be used for trade, resale or other commercial purposes.

idinfo.native: Microsoft Windows XP Version 5.1 (Build 2600) Service Pack 2; ESRI ArcCatalog 9.3.1.3000

dataqual.logic: This parcel data is checked for errors via mapping department. This parcel data is known to have some inaccuracies and/or misrepresentations. Data should only be viewed as complete for the parcels that exist during the current Tax Billing year.
dataqual.complete: When two or more parcels are combined, the old parcel lines are kept for historical reference.

procstep.procdesc: When property lines are altered via a recording instrument and/or two or more parcels are merged. The exhisting parcel lines are cut and pasted into a new polyline feature class for historical reference.

altsys.altenc: Explicit elevation coordinate included with horizontal coordinates

enttyp.enttypd: Feature class polyline that represents a reference to an historical property line.

attrdomv.udom: Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.

distinfo.resdesc: Available to the public as ESRI Shapefiles by CD, DVD or downloadable Data via FTP site
distinfo.distliab: The Geographic Information Systems (GIS) data provided is a public resource of general information. The Tax Parcel information contained within is continually updated by the Gaston County GIS/Mapping staff. The maps and data provided are believed to be accurate and true, but should NOT be considered as a legal document. The GIS data provided by GASTON COUNTY for this web site is made available on the condition that the user willingly agrees to waive any and all claims that may be brought against GASTON COUNTY, its contractors, and/or its employees. By accessing this data you are releasing GASTON COUNTY, its contractors, and its employees from all liability that may occur from any omissions, errors, or inaccuracies in the data.
